The German has won five fewer races than Hamilton this year, but would pinch the title if he wins on Sunday and Hamilton finishes outside the top two.

'It was a great day again today, it all worked out well,' said Rosberg. 'I put a good lap together in the end, but it's only one very small step. It's about the championship, not about the pole.

'I was hoping for a Williams to be between us, it didn't happen, but hopefully that can be the case tomorrow.

'My mindset now is I need to get the job done, to continue with the form I showed at the last race in Brazil. In any case I'm sure it will be a great race.'

